Setup: Create the Root Filesystem
Before running the container, you need a minimal Linux filesystem (Alpine Linux is recommended for its small size).

Run the following commands in your terminal:

```bash
# 1. Create a directory for the container image
mkdir -p container_root

# 2. Download the Alpine Linux Mini RootFS
wget [https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.18/releases/x86_64/alpine-minirootfs-3.18.4-x86_64.tar.gz](https://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.18/releases/x86_64/alpine-minirootfs-3.18.4-x86_64.tar.gz)

# 3. Extract the filesystem
tar -xzf alpine-minirootfs-3.18.4-x86_64.tar.gz -C container_root

# 4. Running the Container
chmod +x mdocker.py
sudo ./mdocker.py run ./container_root /bin/sh
